CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1957, pg. 1, reads: "Rosella Bush Retires After Carrying Mail for 40 Years - Antique Collection - One of 'Rosie' Bush's hobbies is the collection of antiques. Quite handy with tools, she enjoys refinishing them, too.  She poses in an upstairs room of her home beside a Lincoln bed, which she refinished in a year.  Note the spinning wheel, dresser and chandelier.  Many of the antiques she has obtained from farm folk on her mail route."
TitMainTitle: Rosella Bush leaning over large ornate bed with woven coverlet, in bedroom with floral walls and ceiling and spinning wheel
